<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-755-022  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 755 022.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Oct 9 1989 n336 p138(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer Learning Month focuses on K-12 arena.andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>October of 1989 is Computer Learning Month, sponsored by theComputer Learning Foundation.andP;  The month-long focus oncomputer-assisted instruction (CAI) for students in the K-12school market should inspire educational administrators tore-evaluate their computer systems, a bonus for computer resellersdealing heavily in the education marketplace.andP;  Many smaller,independent school districts have already determined budgets forthe coming school year, however.andP;  The increased awarenesssurrounding computer-aided education is important for educationalresellers that, for the first time, have found some educators tobe less than enthusiastic about using computers as educationaltools.andP;  Doubt exists as to whether there is enough concreteevidence to justify the huge expense of building computerclassrooms.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer Learning FoundationSecondary SchoolsComputer-Assisted InstructionElementary SchoolsEducationComputer EducationTeaching.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>